      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i'm just starting to learn music theory and i keep hearing about the circle of fifths. can u explain what it actually is and how i can use it to figure out key signatures?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The Circle of Fifths is a visual diagram that organizes musical keys by their major and minor third notes, directions in clockwise and counterclockwise that represent different relative keys, and the number of sharps or flats in each key signature. To figure out the key of a major scale using this circle, start from the far right (C major, with no sharps or flats) and move clockwise one step for every sharp added to the key or one step counterclockwise for every flat. For a minor key, locate the relative major on its second circle note (a half-step away) and count the sharps or flats corresponding to that same position in the circle.",
